d Stubbs |editor-link=Aelred Stubbs |title=I Write What I Like: A Selection of His Writings |year=1987 |location=London |publisher=Heinemann |isbn=978-0-435-90598-9}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Fatton |first=Robert |year=1986 |title=Black Consciousness in South Africa: The Dialectics of Ideological Resistance to White Supremacy |publisher=State University of New York Press |location=Albany |isbn=978-0887061295}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Gerhart |first=Gail M. |title=Black Power in South Africa: The Evolution of an Ideology |location=Los Angeles |publisher=Greenberg |year=1999 |isbn=978-0520039339}}\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Goodwin |first=June |last2=Schiff |first2=Ben |title=Who Killed Steve Biko?: Exhuming Truth in South Africa |journal=The Nation |date=13 November 1995 |volume=261 |issue=16 |pages=565\u2013568 |issn=0027-8378 |publisher=The Nation Company |location=New York}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Lobban |first=Michael |title=White Man's Justice: South African Political Trials in the Black Consciousness Era |location=Oxford |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=1996 |isbn=978-0198258094}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Magaziner |first=D. |title=The Law and the Prophets: Black Consciousness in South Africa, 1968\u20131977 |location=Athens |publisher=Ohio University Press |year=2010 |isbn=978-0821419175}}\n\n: {{cite book |last1=Pityana |first1=B. |first2=M. |last2=Ramphele |first3=M. |last3=Mpumlwana |first4=L. |last4=Wilson |title=Bounds of Possibility: The Legacy of Steve Biko and Black Consciousness |location=Cape Town |publisher=David Philip |year=1991 |isbn=978-0864862105}}\n\n{{Refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n*[http://www.sbf.org.za/ The Steve Biko Foundation]\n*{{imdb name|8363356}}\n\n{{Pan-Africanism}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Biko, Steve}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:1977 deaths]]\n[[Category:1977 in South Africa]]\n[[Category:20th-century Christians]]\n[[Category:20th-century South African male wr