{"title_page": "Prillwitz", "text_new": "{{dablink|Prillwitz is also the former German name for [[Przelewice, Pyrzyce County|Przelewice]], a village in northwestern Poland.}}\n\n'''Prillwitz''' is a small village in [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]] (Mecklenburg-West Pomerania), on the shores of the lake [[Lieps]], [[Germany]]. It is part of the municipality [[Hohenzieritz]]. It lies approximately 125 kilometres north of [[Berlin]] through the B96 or 205 kilometres through the A20.<ref>[https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode=&q=prillwitz,+germany&sll=53.533778,12.425537&sspn=2.716571,6.70166&ie=UTF8&hq=&hnear=Prillwitz+Hohenzieritz,+Mecklenburg-Strelitz,+Mecklenburg-West+Pomerania,+Germany&z=13 Google Maps]</ref> The town has a church and a small castle converted into a hotel and restaurant.<ref>[http://www.jagdschloss-prillwitz.de/ Jagdschloss Prillwitz]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Prillwitz idols]]\n\n== References ==\n{{commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|53|27|N|13|08|E|display=title|region:DE_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{dablink|Prillwitz is also the former German name for [[Przelewice, Pyrzyce County|Przelewice]], a village in northwestern Poland.}}\n\n'''Prillwitz''' is a small village in [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]] (Mecklenburg-West Pomerania), on the shores of the lake [[Lieps]], [[Germany]]. It is part of the municipality [[Hohenzieritz]]. It lies approximately 125 kilometres north of [[Berlin]] through the B96 or 205 kilometres through the A20.<ref>[https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode=&q=prillwitz,+germany&sll=53.533778,12.425537&sspn=2.716571,6.70166&ie=UTF8&hq=&hnear=Prillwitz+Hohenzieritz,+Mecklenburg-Strelitz,+Mecklenburg-West+Pomerania,+Germany&z=13 Google Maps]</ref> The town has a church and a small castle converted into a hotel and restaurant.<ref>[http://www.jagdschloss-prillwitz.de/ Jagdschloss Prillwitz]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Prillwitz idols]]\n\n== References ==\n{{commonscat}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|53|27|N|13|08|E|display=title|region:DE_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prillwitz"}
{"title_page": "Priesitz", "text_new": "{{Infobox German location\n|type = Stadtteil\n|Town = [[Bad Schmiedeberg]]\n|image_photo       = \n|image_coa            = \n|coordinates       = {{coord|51|42|N|12|49|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|image_plan          = \n|state        = Sachsen-Anhalt\n|district         = Wittenberg\n|elevation              = 73\n|area            = 10.09\n|population         = 271\n|Stand             = 2006-12-31\n|postal_code               = 06909\n|area_code           = 034926\n|licence               = WB\n|Adresse-Verband   = Markt 10<br>06905 Bad Schmiedeberg\n}}\n\n'''Priesitz''' is a village and a former municipality in [[Wittenberg (district)|Wittenberg]] district in [[Saxony-Anhalt]], [[Germany]]. Since 1 July 2009, it is part of the town [[Bad Schmiedeberg]].\n\n== Geography ==\nPriesitz lies about 25 kilometers southeast of [[Lutherstadt Wittenberg]] in the glacial valley of the [[Elbe]] at the edge of the [[D\u00fcben Heath Nature Park]].\n\n=== Subdivisions===\nPriesitz has one of these: Sachau.\n\n== History ==\nPriesitz had its first documentary mention in 1290.\n\n== Regular events ==\nEvery year, the Lake Festival (''Seefest'') is held in early July as a village festival.\n\n== Economy and transportation==\nFederal Highway (''Bundesstra\u00dfe'') B 182, which joins [[Torgau]] and [[Wittenberg]] lies about 0.5&nbsp;km away. The railway line between Torgau and [[Pretzsch (Elbe)|Pretzsch]] has a stop in Sachau.\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.bad-schmiedeberg.de Verwaltungsgemeinschaft's website]\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Saxony-Anhalt]]\n[[Category:Bezirk Halle]]\n\n\n{{Wittenberg-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox German location\n|type = Stadtteil\n|Town = [[Bad Schmiedeberg]]\n|image_photo       = \n|image_coa            = \n|coordinates       = {{coord|51|42|N|12|49|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|image_plan          = \n|state        = Sachsen-Anhalt\n|district         = Wittenberg\n|elevation              = 73\n|area            = 10.09\n|population         = 271\n|Stand             = 2006-12-31\n|postal_code               = 06909\n|area_code           = 034926\n|licence               = WB\n|Adresse-Verband   = Markt 10<br>06905 Bad Schmiedeberg\n}}\n\n'''Priesitz''' is a village and a former municipality in [[Wittenberg (district)|Wittenberg]] district in [[Saxony-Anhalt]], [[Germany]]. Since 1 July 2009, it is part of the town [[Bad Schmiedeberg]].\n\n== Geography ==\nPriesitz lies about 25 kilometers southeast of [[Lutherstadt Wittenberg]] in the glacial valley of the [[Elbe]] at the edge of the [[D\u00fcben Heath Nature Park]].\n\n=== Subdivisions===\nPriesitz has one of these: Sachau.\n\n== History ==\nPriesitz had its first documentary mention in 1290.\n\n== Regular events ==\nEvery year, the Lake Festival (''Seefest'') is held in early July as a village festival.\n\n== Economy and transportation==\nFederal Highway (''Bundesstra\u00dfe'') B 182, which joins [[Torgau]] and [[Wittenberg]] lies about 0.5&nbsp;km away. The railway line between Torgau and [[Pretzsch (Elbe)|Pretzsch]] has a stop in Sachau.\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.bad-schmiedeberg.de Verwaltungsgemeinschaft's website]\n\n[[Category:Villages in Saxony-Anhalt]]\n[[Category:Bezirk Halle]]\n\n{{Wittenberg-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Priesitz"}
